<p>easy there the King arrived &amp; crossed by us to the Pavilion, for we were on the extreme left:  More standing at ease while he reviewed the troops starting from the extreme right<br/>It was a magnificent sight to see the thousands of troops lined up on that huge field<br/>I happened to be in the second section &amp; was therefore quite near to him when he arrived at our end.<br/>Then came the march past.<br/>The troops went to the right extreme of the field &amp; wheeled round so as to come back pa the Pavilion</p>
